    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/5–2049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Legation in Switzerland</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-20T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss> 110. For Lausanne. We agree (<gloss
                        target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 153<note n="1" xml:id="d677fn1">See
                        footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_1038">p. 1038</ref>.</note>) ur proposal France
                    and Turkey join US and UK in concerted program urge Israel and Arabs face
                    refugee problem constructively through repatriation and resettlement. Pls
                    outline to Yalcin and Boisanger genl nature our approaches Israel and Arabs
                        (<gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> Apr 29, 5 p. m. and <gloss
                        target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss> 85, Apr 28), informing them Dept concurs
                    your view re desirability parallel approaches by French and Turkish Govts and
                    requesting that they so inform their Govts earliest opportunity. In absence
                    instrs this subject to French and Turk missions Washington, we believe approach
                    by you speedier and more effective.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
